Share this on WhatsAppSpread the loveAhead of the clash against the Black Stars of Ghana, the Super Eagles of Nigeria have been urged not to lose the first leg of their game.
This plea came from gospel singer, Nathaniel Bassey on Tuesday on his Instagram page.
He said, “Dear super eagles! Per World Cup qualifiers
Whatever you do, don’t loose the first leg ooo…. Selah!”
The Super Eagles are set to face Ghana on Friday at the Baba Yara Stadium, with the return leg scheduled for Tuesday at the Moshood Abiola Stadium in Abuja.
